  "prompt": "Can I get my drivers license if I'm 17 in india?",
  "response": "In India, the age eligibility for obtaining a driver's license depends on the type of vehicle you wish to drive:\n\n1. **Two-Wheelers (Motorcycles/Scooters)**:  \n   - You can apply for a **Learner's License** at the age of **16**.  \n   - To obtain a **Permanent License**, you must be at least **17 years old**, but the license will only be valid after you turn **18**.\n\n2. **Four-Wheelers (Cars)**:  \n   - You must be at least **18 years old** to apply for both a **Learner's License** and a **Permanent License**.\n\n### Summary:\n- If you are **17 years old**, you can only apply for a **Permanent License for two-wheelers**, but it will become valid only after you turn **18**.\n- For **four-wheelers**, you must wait until you are **18 years old**.\n  \nAlways ensure you follow the necessary legal procedures and have proper documentation when applying for a driver's license.",
